The paper deals with finding the mode and top-frequent elements in a dynamic array corresponding to a log stream, which is a problem related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an algorithm for profiling dynamic arrays, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, making cs.DB (Databases) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions answering queries on statistics, which is related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses computational complexity and performance, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for processing data streams, which is related to stream processing and real-time systems, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
